<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8437> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8437" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 730" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2287> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2287" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He was sent along with L. Manlius to King Antiochus to exact the oath ratifying the treaty (Polyb. 21.43.1-2; Liv. 38.39.1; App. Syr. 39, a Tribune of the Soldiers ?). Killed while returning with Manlius through Thrace (Liv. 38.41.3, 46.7, and 49.8)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2286> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2286" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The ten Legates assisted Manlius in concluding the treaty with Antiochus and the settlement of Asia Minor, and returned with him (Polyb. 21.4-45; 22.5; Liv. 38.38-40, and 45-46)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2263> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2263" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "An embassy of ten members sent to assist Manlius Vulso in implementing the treaty with Antiochus and in completing the settlement of Asia Minor (Liv. 37.55.7; 38.38.1, and 40.1, and 44.9-47, and 54.6; cf. Polyb. 21.24.9, and 16.17; see 188, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2260> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2260" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appian (Syr. 39) mistakenly calls Thermus a {Gr}." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2259> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2259" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Though Willems is compelled to admit that this embassy consists in any case of an unusual proportion of senior members of the Senate, he attempts to fit it to his regular pattern (Sénat 2.506) by claiming: 1. that Aemilius Paullus was not the famous member of the family (but see above, note 3); 2. that Lentulus was not the Pr. of 203 but another, the Cos. of 162 (who was too young and whose career, as Münzer has shown, RE no. 214, he has reported incorrectly, Sénat 1.347, no. 216); and 3. that Aelius Tubero was not the Pr. of 201 but someone otherwise unknown. Münzer suggests that Lentulus{365} is a mistake for Cethegus, Pr. 185 and Cos. 181, and since the two men are confused in Liv. 40.18.1 this remains a possibility. However it is unnecessary, for with the identification of Aemilius Paullus the commission is seen to consist of eight consulars or praetorians, and evidently may have consisted wholly of men of curule rank. Therefore in spite of the disarangement of the two final names it seems preferable to identify Lentulus with the Praetor of 203 and Tubero with the Praetor of 201. As we know the names of only three senatorial commissions of ten men during this period and possess the complete list of only this one, the basis for Willems' generalization regarding the pattern remains rather tenuous." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2214> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2214" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Liguria (see 191, Promagistrates). Instructed by the Senate to give over his army to Scipio Nasica (Liv. 37.2.5), and denied a triumph upon his return (37.46.1-2). See Grueber, CRRBM 2.302; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.181f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2182> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2182" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Liguria (Liv. 36.38.1-4, and 40.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2160> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2160" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His command extended for a year, he won a victory over the Ligurians near Pisa (Liv. 35.20.6; 35.21.7-11)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2119> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2119" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Nep. Hann. 8.1; Liv. 34.54.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 454f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; and on Minucius, Frontin. Str. 1.5.16. Merula was assigned the Gallic province and made war on the Boii (Liv. 34.55.6, and 56.12-13; 35.4-5, and 6.5-9), but was refused a triumph (Liv. 35.8). Minucius campaigned against the Ligurians, using Pisa as a base, but with little success (Liv. 34.55.6, and 56.3-7; 35.3.1-6, and 6.1-4, and 11.1-13; cf. FOR 1.167-169; Frontin. Str. 1.5.16; Oros. 4.20.17)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2116> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2116" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 197, Special Commissions. In this, the last year of the three year term of these commissioners, are mentioned the colonies authorized{346} in 197, Puteoli, Volturnum, Liternum, Salernum, Buxentum (Liv. 34.45.1-2). On Puteoli, see also CIL 1.2.698. On all the colonies, see Jerome, Chr. ad ann. 191, p. 136 Helm." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2080> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2080" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (?) in Hither Spain (Act. Tr. Cap.: pr[ocos- - -], and Tol.: p[rocos-], Degrassi 78f., 338f., 552). After a success at Turda, he returned to celebrate a triumph (Liv. 33.44.4-5; 34.10.5-7; Act. Tr. Cap. and Tol..)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2028> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2028" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 33.24.2 Provinces and armies 33.26.1-4, and 43.7-8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2025> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2025" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Were commissioned for three years to settle colonies at the mouths of the Volturnus and the Liternus, at Puteoli, Castrum Salerni, and Buxentum (Liv. 32.29.3-4; cf. 34.45.2; Vell. 1.15.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1992> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1992" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 32.27.8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1907> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1907" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Opposed Lentulus' desire for the province of Africa (Liv. 30.40.9-16), and carried a plebiscite confirming peace with Carthage (30.43.2-3; cf. Polyb. 15.18-19; Dio fr. 57.82-83; Zon. 9.14; see Promagistrates, on Scipio)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1896> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1896" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Scipio in Africa (App. Lib. 36; cf. Frontin. Str. 1.8.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1895> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1895" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Münzer (RE) accepts the part played by this Tribune in the African campaign even though the evidence of Appian is often unreliable (see also De Sanctis 3.2.601ff.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10163> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10163" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Hispania Citeriore. MRR I.341, Itgenshorst no. 171, Rich no. 170." .
